(1) If any member is, after due inquiry, found by the Disciplinary Committee to have been guilty of infamous conduct in any professional respect, the Disciplinary Committee may, if it considers appropriate, impose one or more of the following penalties— (a) direct the de-registration of that member ; (b) censure such member ; (c) warn the member and suspend any further action against that member for one year depending on that member 's conduct during the suspension of such action; (d) order the member to pay a fine to the Council and any costs incidental to the proceedings incurred by the Council ; (e) expel the member ; or (f) take such other action as it may consider necessary.
